(161, 'of_template', 'a:211:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:\"name\";s:14:\"Most Important\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"heading\";}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:25:\"Real Estate or Car Sales?\";s:4:\"desc\";s:140:\"<strong style=\'color: red;\'>IMOPORTANT: After your choice, please refresh this page before making any more changes in Theme Options</strong>\";s:2:\"id\";s:7:\"wp_site\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:2:{i:0;s:11:\"Real Estate\";i:1;s:9:\"Car Sales\";}s:3:\"std\";s:11:\"Real Estate\";}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"Print Page\";s:4:\"desc\";s:295:\"What is your listings \'Print\' page? This is the page that is specially formatted for nice printing output for your listings. (Note: you must create a \'Page\'. Give it a title (anything you like). Also give it the Page Template name called \'Print Listing\'. That page will appear in this dropdown.)\";s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"wp_printpage\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:2:{i:0;s:14:\"Select a page:\";i:1;s:18:\"Página de exemplo\";}s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:2:{s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"Homepage Layouts\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"heading\";}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:39:\"What to show under slideshow (1st area)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:162:\"Under the slideshow on the homepage, to the right of the left column search area, are 3 main sections: Recent Listins, 3 widgetized blocks, and Recent Blog posts.\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"wp_homepage_layout1\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:3:{i:0;s:15:\"Recent Listings\";i:1;s:7:\"Widgets\";i:2;s:10:\"Blog Posts\";}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:39:\"What to show under slideshow (2nd area)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:162:\"Under the slideshow on the homepage, to the right of the left column search area, are 3 main sections: Recent Listins, 3 widgetized blocks, and Recent Blog posts.\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"wp_homepage_layout2\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:7:\"Widgets\";i:1;s:15:\"Recent Listings\";i:2;s:10:\"Blog Posts\";i:3;s:9:\"[nothing]\";}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:39:\"What to show under slideshow (3rd area)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:162:\"Under the slideshow on the homepage, to the right of the left column search area, are 3 main sections: Recent Listins, 3 widgetized blocks, and Recent Blog posts.\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"wp_homepage_layout3\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:10:\"Blog Posts\";i:1;s:7:\"Widgets\";i:2;s:15:\"Recent Listings\";i:3;s:9:\"[nothing]\";}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:29:\"Widget layout on the homepage\";s:4:\"desc\";s:297:\"If you opt to show the widgetized area on the homepage, you have 4 layout choices.<br /><br />1. 3 equal size widget areas<br /><br />2. Two widget areas, right one twice as wide as the left.<br /><br />3. Two widget areas, left one  twice as wide as the right.<br /><br />4. One wide widget area.\";s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"wp_widgetlayout\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:8:\"Layout 1\";i:1;s:8:\"Layout 2\";i:2;s:8:\"Layout 3\";i:3;s:8:\"Layout 4\";}}i:8;a:2:{s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"Appearance\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"heading\";}i:9;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:17:\"Main Color Scheme\";s:4:\"desc\";s:346:\"Set the colour scheme for the theme.  This color will be used for the site background, headers, and buttons.  It is best to choose relatively dark colors, otherwise some headers will appear too light against light backgrounds.  If you do choose a very light color, you will have to edit some CSS so some text is legible against light backgrounds.\";s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"wp_color_scheme\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"color\";s:3:\"std\";s:7:\"#a81c1c\";}i:10;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:46:\"Text color (if main color scheme is too light)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:172:\"If your color scheme (above) is fairly light, then the standard white text that is sometimes on top of it may be hard to read. Choose a darker color here to override white.\";s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"wp_textcolor\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"color\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:11;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:15:\"Logo URL (Main)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:106:\"Enter the link to your logo image.  Simply upload image with Wordpress, and copy/paste the final URL here.\";s:2:\"id\";s:7:\"wp_logo\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"upload\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:12;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"Logo width\";s:4:\"desc\";s:301:\"Width of logo area. If you make this more than 300, then the width will cause side scrolling when viewed on small very small mobile devices. So if no side scrolling is important, then try to keep your logo under 300 px wide. If this setting is 300 and your logo is wider, then it will get clipped off.\";s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"wp_logowidth\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:3:\"300\";}i:13;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:15:\"Logo position X\";s:4:\"desc\";s:61:\"Tweak the X/Y position of the logo (X is horizontal position)\";s:2:\"id\";s:9:\"wp_logo_x\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:1:\"0\";}i:14;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:15:\"Logo position Y\";s:4:\"desc\";s:109:\"Tweak the X/Y position of the logo (Y is vertical position).  Negative numbers go up, positive numbers, down.\";s:2:\"id\";s:9:\"wp_logo_y\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:1:\"0\";}i:15;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:13:\"Header height\";s:4:\"desc\";s:103:\"Height of the header area. If your logo is large, you can increase this number to allow for more space.\";s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"wp_headerheight\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:3:\"150\";}i:16;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"Background Color\";s:4:\"desc\";s:260:\"The background color is seen to the left and right of the site, with screens wider than 960px. This color can be combined with the next setting, \'Background Image\'. In this case, the color will only show if the image tiling is not filling up the entire screen.\";s:2:\"id\";s:18:\"wp_backgroundcolor\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"color\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:17;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"Background Image\";s:4:\"desc\";s:637:\"The background image is seen to the left and right of the sige, with screens wider than 960px.  This image can be combined with the previous setting, \'Background Color\'. The image will overlap any chosen color<br /><br />Tip: this theme doesn\'t include any backgrounds, because there are just too many styles and designs possible. Instead, there are many websites that offer free seamless background images. My favorite is: <a target=_blank  href=\'http://subtlepatterns.com/\'>http://subtlepatterns.com/</a>. Just download, unzip, and upload here.<br ><br />You can use a light or dark color and it will not affect the legibility of text.\";s:2:\"id\";s:18:\"wp_backgroundimage\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"upload\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:18;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:23:\"Background Image Tiling\";s:4:\"desc\";s:67:\"Repeat the background image on the X axis, Y axis, or don\'t repeat.\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"wp_backgroundrepeat\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:6:\"repeat\";i:1;s:8:\"repeat-x\";i:2;s:8:\"repeat-y\";i:3;s:9:\"no-repeat\";}s:3:\"std\";s:6:\"repeat\";}i:19;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:19:\"Background Position\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";s:2:\"id\";s:21:\"wp_backgroundposition\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:9:{i:0;s:8:\"left top\";i:1;s:11:\"left center\";i:2;s:11:\"left bottom\";i:3;s:9:\"right top\";i:4;s:12:\"right center\";i:5;s:12:\"right bottom\";i:6;s:10:\"center top\";i:7;s:13:\"center center\";i:8;s:13:\"center bottom\";}s:3:\"std\";s:8:\"left top\";}i:20;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:21:\"Background Attachment\";s:4:\"desc\";s:78:\"Do you want the background image to scroll along with the page, or stay fixed?\";s:2:\"id\";s:23:\"wp_backgroundattachment\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:2:{i:0;s:5:\"fixed\";i:1;s:6:\"scroll\";}s:3:\"std\";s:5:\"fixed\";}i:21;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"Header Color\";s:4:\"desc\";s:498:\"The header color for the site. If no color is chosen, it will default to white. This chosen color will override the optional header background image setting below.<br /><br />Tip: enter \'transparent\' if you wan