 taken care of. This overrides any other stylesheets. eg: a.button{color:green}. The CSS is placed in the head of every page, thus overriding the global style.css\";s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"wp_customcss\";s:4:\"type\";s:8:\"textarea\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:36;a:2:{s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"General Settings\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"heading\";}i:37;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:44:\"Contact form Shortcode (for Contact Us page)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:136:\"Contact Form 7 Plugin shortcode for the Contact Us page. To create this page, create a new Page, and choose the \'Contact\' Page Template.\";s:2:\"id\";s:25:\"wp_contactuspageshortcode\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:38;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:27:\"Google Map of your location\";s:4:\"desc\";s:105:\"Full address, city state, and zip/postal code, etc for your location.  To be used in the Contact Us page.\";s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"wp_contactmap\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:39;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:30:\"Blog posts per page (homepage)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:145:\"If you are showing blog posts on the homepage, how many do you want to show? (note: layout is 4 items per row, so multiples of 4 is a good idea.)\";s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"wp_blognumber\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:1:\"6\";}i:40;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"Compare Page\";s:4:\"desc\";s:187:\"Your \'Compare\' listings page.  (Note: you must create a \'Page\' for Compare. Give it a title. Also give it the Page Template name called \'Compare\'. That page will appear in this dropdown.)\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"wp_comparepage\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:2:{i:0;s:14:\"Select a page:\";i:1;s:18:\"Página de exemplo\";}s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:41;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:35:\"Recent Listings Quantity (homepage)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:118:\"How many recent listings do you want to show in the homepage? (this is the thumbnail image version of Recent Listings)\";s:2:\"id\";s:28:\"wp_recentlistingsnumber_home\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:1:\"3\";}i:42;a:5:{s:4:\"